  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: working tree clean, branch `work/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1`, baseline build passes, task 030 ✅ + task 032 in flight (we extend `GateEndpoints.cs` from 032). Load knowledge. Declare RIGOR LEVEL: FULL.</step>
    <step order="1">Read ADR-028 (Spaarke Auth v2), `auth-deployment-setup.md`, and task 030's contract. Understand the HMAC envelope shape required by downstream Spaarke webhook consumers (if any pattern exists; otherwise define canonically here).</step>
    <step order="2">Create `WebhookGateSignatureValidator.cs` — pure validator class. Two methods: `SignOutbound(body, timestamp, secret) =&gt; signature` and `ValidateInbound(body, timestamp, signature, secret) =&gt; bool`. Use `HMACSHA256` from BCL. Constant-time compare via `CryptographicOperations.FixedTimeEquals`. Timestamp skew check (&lt;5 min).</step>
    <step order="3">Create `WebhookGateResolver.cs` — ctor injects `IHttpClientFactory`, `IKeyVaultSecretProvider`, `WebhookGateSignatureValidator`, `IAuditService`, `IActionRegistryService` (to look up Action's webhook URL + allowlist), `ILogger`. `ResolveAsync`: validate URL against allowlist → fetch HMAC secret → sign envelope → POST → audit `Pending` → return `Pending`.</step>
    <step order="4">Build canonical envelope JSON: `{ correlationId, actionRunId, toolDispatchId, gateType, requestedByUserId, surfaceHint, payload, expiresAtUtc }`. Use `JsonSerializer` with stable property ordering (`PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase`, `PropertyNameCaseInsensitive = false`).</step>
    <step order="5">Extend `GateEndpoints.cs` (from task 032) with `POST /api/ai/gates/webhook/callback`. Apply a custom endpoint filter `WebhookHmacValidationFilter` that validates the `X-Spaarke-Signature` + `X-Spaarke-Timestamp` headers before the endpoint executes. On invalid signature: audit `Rejected` w/ reason `"hmac validation failed"`, return `Results.Problem(statusCode: 401, title: "Invalid signature", ...)`. On valid: resolve the pending gate via `IGateApprovalChannel.ResolvePendingAsync` (extending channel from task 032 to support webhook resolution too — OR introduce `IWebhookGateResolutionStore` if cleaner).</step>
    <step order="6">Configure `HttpClient` for outbound via named factory `WebhookGate` with sensible defaults: 10-sec timeout, retry only on transient errors (no retry on 4xx), no auth header beyond HMAC headers (the receiving endpoint authenticates US, not the other way around).</step>
    <step order="7">Wire Key Vault secret loading: secret name `action-engine-webhook-hmac-key`. Document the deployment procedure in `notes/deployment/033-webhook-hmac-secret-rotation.md` (manual rotation in MVP; automation deferred).</step>
    <step order="8">Register DI in `AddGatesFeature()`: `services.AddHttpClient("WebhookGate", ...); services.AddSingleton&lt;WebhookGateSignatureValidator&gt;(); services.AddKeyedScoped&lt;IGateResolver, WebhookGateResolver&gt;(GateType.Conditional);`. ADR-010 budget check.</step>
    <step order="9">Write unit tests:
      (a) `Validator_SignAndValidate_RoundTrip` — sign body+timestamp, validate succeeds.
      (b) `Validator_TamperedBody_ValidationFails`.
      (c) `Validator_ExpiredTimestamp_ValidationFails` (skew &gt; 5 min).
      (d) `Validator_ConstantTimeCompare_NoTimingLeak` — assert use of `FixedTimeEquals`.
      (e) `Resolver_HappyPath_PostsSignedAndReturnsPending`.
      (f) `Resolver_DisallowedUrl_RejectsImmediately` — URL not in Action allowlist → audit reject, return `Rejected`.
      (g) `Resolver_HttpClientFails_HandlesGracefully` — surface failure as audit + return `Rejected` (do NOT throw out of `ResolveAsync`).
      (h) `Callback_ValidHmac_ResolvesPending` — endpoint integration test.
      (i) `Callback_InvalidHmac_Returns401AndAuditsRejection`.
      (j) `Callback_DuplicateCallback_IsIdempotent`.</step>
    <step order="10">Build + run tests: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` exits 0; `dotnet test` passes new tests. Measure publish-size delta; expect &lt; 0.1 MB. Record in `notes/measurements/033-publish-size-delta.md`.</step>
    <step order="9.5">Run quality gates: `code-review` (security-critical — constant-time compare verified, replay protection verified, no plaintext secrets, ProblemDetails correctness), `adr-check` (ADR-001/008/010/013/015/019/028/029). MANDATORY human escalation per CLAUDE.md §6 if any concern about HMAC implementation correctness.</step>
    <step order="10.5">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: 033 ✅. Update `current-task.md`.</step>
    <step order="11">Commit + push. Add `notes/deployment/033-webhook-hmac-secret-rotation.md` covering rotation procedure for Ops.</step>
  </steps>

