  <notes>
    Security review is MANDATORY at Step 9.5 — per CLAUDE.md §6 "security-sensitive code" triggers human escalation. The HMAC implementation is the load-bearing primitive; mistakes here have outsized impact.

    Resume coupling with `IGateApprovalChannel` from task 032: webhook callbacks resolve the same pending-TCS dictionary the in-chat resolver uses. This unifies the resolution path. If unification proves awkward (e.g., session-bound TCS doesn't fit webhook lifecycle), introduce `IWebhookGateResolutionStore` as a separate scoped/singleton store and document the deviation in `notes/decisions/033-resolution-store-design.md`.

    URL allowlist storage: Action Definition's `governance` JSON block has a `webhookAllowedUrls: string[]` field; the resolver loads via `IActionRegistryService.GetActionAsync(actionRunId.ActionId)`. Phase 4 task 040 finalizes the Action governance block schema; coordinate if changes needed.

    Outbound `HttpClient` MUST NOT follow redirects (`AllowAutoRedirect = false`) — redirects bypass the URL allowlist.
  </notes>

